{"id":4429,"date":"2020-01-08T11:06:51","date_gmt":"2020-01-08T11:06:51","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.violet.care\/?p=4429"},"modified":"2020-01-10T09:29:59","modified_gmt":"2020-01-10T09:29:59","slug":"emergency-support-tips","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/localhost\/emergency-support-tips\/","title":{"rendered":"Emergency Support Tips"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><br><br>Here are some shortcuts to contact 999 \/ 112 in an emergency using your mobile phone. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong> <\/strong><br><br><strong>iPhone <\/strong><br><em>iPhone 8 or later<\/em><br><br>Press and hold the side button and\u00a0one of the Volume buttons until the Emergency\u00a0SOS slider appears.\u00a0<br> Drag the Emergency\u00a0SOS\u00a0slider to call emergency services. <br><br><em>iPhone 7 or earlier:\u00a0<\/em><br> Rapidly press the side\u00a0(or top)\u00a0button five times. The Emergency SOS slider will appear.<br>Drag the Emergency\u00a0SOS\u00a0slider to\u00a0call emergency\u00a0services.<br><br><strong>Android <\/strong><br>Samsung Galaxy: <br>SOS Messages: <br>Open your phone\u2019s settings, go to \u201cPersonal,\u201d \u00a0select \u201cPrivacy and Emergency,\u201d and click \u201cSend SOS Messages.\u201d<br>Enable the feature by clicking the toggle at the top right. It will prompt you to agree to a disclaimer. Once you accept the terms, you will be able to set up SOS Messages.<br><br>Click \u201cSend messages to\u201d to select up to four emergency contacts to receive your emergency alerts. <br><br><strong>Apps<\/strong><br>Suggested apps that both contact and can record various details of your emergency quickly are: <br>&#8211; Shake2Alert<br>-SOS Emergency App<br>-Emergency button [SOS] <br>-Shake2Safety<br><br><strong>Texts: <\/strong><br>You can text 999 to request services. <br>In order to do this, first you must register by texting 999. <br> You will get a reply and will then need to follow the instructions you are sent. <br>The text system is meant to be used only when voice calls cannot be made and the system does not guarantee that texts will be delivered so users should wait until they receive a reply from the emergency services before assuming help has been summoned. <br><br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/www.violet.care\/wp-content\/uploads\/ios12-iphone-x-place-emergency-call-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4438\" width=\"275\" height=\"552\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost\/wp-content\/uploads\/ios12-iphone-x-place-emergency-call-1.jpg 640w, http:\/\/localhost\/wp-content\/uploads\/ios12-iphone-x-place-emergency-call-1-585x1175.jpg 585w, http:\/\/localhost\/wp-content\/uploads\/ios12-iphone-x-place-emergency-call-1-100x201.jpg 100w, http:\/\/localhost\/wp-content\/uploads\/ios12-iphone-x-place-emergency-call-1-600x1206.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 275px) 100vw, 275px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Here are some shortcuts to contact 999 \/ 112 in an emergency using your mobile phone. iPhone iPhone 8 or later Press and hold the side button and\u00a0one of the Volume buttons until the Emergency\u00a0SOS slider appears.\u00a0 Drag the Emergency\u00a0SOS\u00a0slider to call emergency services. iPhone 7 or earlier:\u00a0 Rapidly press the side\u00a0(or top)\u00a0button five times. [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":14,"featured_media":4438,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"spay_email":""},"categories":[7],"tags":[1126,1125],"yst_prominent_words":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"http:\/\/localhost\/wp-content\/uploads\/ios12-iphone-x-place-emergency-call-1.jpg","_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4429"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/localho